## Scoring Methodology

The composite SEO + GEO Score (0–100) is a weighted average of six category scores:

| Category | Weight | What It Measures |
|---|---|---|
| **AI Citability** | 25% | How quotable/extractable content is for AI systems |
| **Brand Authority** | 20% | Third-party mentions on Reddit, Wikipedia, YouTube, LinkedIn |
| **Content E-E-A-T** | 20% | Author credentials, original data, freshness |
| **Technical Foundations** | 15% | CWV, AI crawler access, llms.txt, SSR, mobile, security |
| **Structured Data** | 10% | Schema.org completeness, JSON-LD validation |
| **Platform Optimization** | 10% | Readiness for Google AIO, ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, Bing Copilot |

**Score bands:** 90–100 Excellent · 75–89 Good · 60–74 Fair · 40–59 Poor · 0–39 Critical.

**Issue severity:** Critical (blocked AI crawlers, no SSR, site-wide errors) · High (key crawlers blocked, no llms.txt, no Q&A structure) · Medium (partial blocking, thin bios) · Low (minor schema errors, alt text gaps).

## Output Directory

All output files go to `~/geo-seo-projects/[domain]/` — never into the website project being audited.

```bash
DOMAIN=$(echo "[url]" | sed 's|https\?://||' | sed 's|/.*||')
OUTPUT_DIR="$HOME/geo-seo-projects/$DOMAIN"
mkdir -p "$OUTPUT_DIR"
```

**llms.txt special handling:** After writing `~/geo-seo-projects/[domain]/llms.txt`, also check if a `public/` directory exists in the current working directory. If so, copy `llms.txt` and `llms-full.txt` there for immediate deployment.

